revision.text: Possibly: The History of the Rebellion and Civil Wars in England, Begun in the Year 1641. With the precedent passages, and actions, that contributed thereunto, and the happy end, and conclusion thereof by the King's blessed Restoration, and return upon the 29th of May, in the year 1660. Written by the Right Honourable Edward Earl of Clarendon, Late Lord High Chancellor of England, Privy Councellor in the Reigns of King Charles the First and the Second.
